<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
The song of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" genus="Lyristes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lyristes plebejus" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" rank="species" species="plebejus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Lyristes plebejus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very complex structure (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F5781191" captionText="Figure 11. Calling song of Lyristes plebejus. (A) spectrogram and oscillogram of one phrase of the calling song; (B) oscillogram of the last part of the phrase and beginning of a new one corresponding to the inverted window in (A)." figureDoi=".figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/406946" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">11</figureCitation>
). It is a continuous repetition of phrases (duration 7-30 s) without a pause lasting for many minutes. Each phrase can be divided into three parts. The first two parts consist of a fast sequence of short echemes (SE) and the third of a steady buzz (
<bibRefCitation author="Gogala, Matija" journalOrPublisher="Kataloge des Oberoesterreichischen Landesmuseums, Neue Folge, Denisia, 4" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5742831" refString="Gogala, Matija, 2002. Zikaden: Leafhoppers, Planthoppers and Cicadas (Insecta: Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha). Kataloge des Oberoesterreichischen Landesmuseums, Neue Folge, Denisia, 4" title="Zikaden: Leafhoppers, Planthoppers and Cicadas (Insecta: Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha)" year="2002">Gogala 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Joermann, G" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="283 - 296" refId="B5743140" refString="Joermann, G, Schneider, H, 1987. The songs of four species of cicada in Yugoslavia (Homoptera: Cicadidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger 219 (5/6): 283 - 296" title="The songs of four species of cicada in Yugoslavia (Homoptera: Cicadidae)" volume="219" year="1987">Joermann and Schneider 1987</bibRefCitation>
). In the first part, which extends over half of the phrase, 30-240 SE are repeated without pause. This is followed by the transition in the second part, which consists of 25-80 SE, separated by intervals of 15-30 ms. The echeme period (85 ms) is constant over almost the entire first two phrases. Finally, the transition occurs in the third part (duration 1.5-3.0 s) which is characterised by the loss of the echeme structure and has become a steady buzz (
<bibRefCitation author="Joermann, G" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="283 - 296" refId="B5743140" refString="Joermann, G, Schneider, H, 1987. The songs of four species of cicada in Yugoslavia (Homoptera: Cicadidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger 219 (5/6): 283 - 296" title="The songs of four species of cicada in Yugoslavia (Homoptera: Cicadidae)" volume="219" year="1987">Joermann and Schneider 1987</bibRefCitation>
). In the first and second part of the phrase, there is an amplitude modulation of the echemes, which is higher in the first part than in the second part (
<bibRefCitation author="Joermann, G" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="283 - 296" refId="B5743140" refString="Joermann, G, Schneider, H, 1987. The songs of four species of cicada in Yugoslavia (Homoptera: Cicadidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger 219 (5/6): 283 - 296" title="The songs of four species of cicada in Yugoslavia (Homoptera: Cicadidae)" volume="219" year="1987">Joermann and Schneider 1987</bibRefCitation>
). The bandwidth measured 10 dB below the maximum is fairly uniform and ranges from 4.4 kHz to 8.34 kHz, but there is some variation in peak frequency between the phrases (
<bibRefCitation author="Joermann, G" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="283 - 296" refId="B5743140" refString="Joermann, G, Schneider, H, 1987. The songs of four species of cicada in Yugoslavia (Homoptera: Cicadidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger 219 (5/6): 283 - 296" title="The songs of four species of cicada in Yugoslavia (Homoptera: Cicadidae)" volume="219" year="1987">Joermann and Schneider 1987</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
