<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" genus="Lyristes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lyristes plebejus" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" rank="species" species="plebejus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Lyristes plebejus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F5781060" captionText="Figure 8. Lyristes plebejus male." figureDoi=".figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/406830" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">8</figureCitation>
) is the second largest European cicada after the south-eastern European species 
<taxonomicName genus="Lyristes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lyristes gemellus" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" rank="species" species="gemellus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Lyristes gemellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boulard, 1988 and has a very loud and distinct song (
<bibRefCitation author="Hertach, Thomas" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="229 - 269" refId="B6075365" refString="Hertach, Thomas, Nagel, Peter, 2013. Cicadas in Switzerland: a scientific overview of the historic and current knowledge of a popular taxon (Hemiptera: Cicadidae). Revue suisse de Zoologie 120 (2): 229 - 269" title="Cicadas in Switzerland: a scientific overview of the historic and current knowledge of a popular taxon (Hemiptera: Cicadidae)" volume="120" year="2013">Hertach and Nagel 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The species occurs mainly in closed high shrubland and woodland on various plants, such as olive trees, pines, oaks, as well as on fruit trees (
<bibRefCitation author="Sueur, Jerome" journalOrPublisher="Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="177 - 187" refId="B5743742" refString="Sueur, Jerome, Puissant, Stephane, Simoes, Paula Cristina, Seabra, Sofia G, Boulard, Michel, Quartau, Jose Alberto, 2004. Cicadas from Portugal: revised list of species with eco-ethological data (Homoptera: Cicadidae). Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 35 (2): 177 - 187" title="Cicadas from Portugal: revised list of species with eco-ethological data (Homoptera: Cicadidae)" volume="35" year="2004">Sueur et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Drosopoulos, Sakis" journalOrPublisher="CRC Press, Taylor &amp; Francis, Boca Raton" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5742769" refString="Drosopoulos, Sakis, Eliopoulos, Elias, Tsakalou, Penelope, 2005. Insect sounds and communication: Physiology, behaviour, ecology, and evolution. CRC Press, Taylor &amp; Francis, Boca Raton" title="Insect sounds and communication: Physiology, behaviour, ecology, and evolution" year="2005">Drosopoulos et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Simoes, Paula Cristina" journalOrPublisher="Biologia, Section Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="961 - 965" refId="B5743652" refString="Simoes, Paula Cristina, Quartau, Jose Alberto, 2013. Distribution of cicadas of the genus Lyristes (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) in the eastern Mediterranean area. Biologia, Section Zoology 68 (5): 961 - 965" title="Distribution of cicadas of the genus Lyristes (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) in the eastern Mediterranean area" volume="68" year="2013">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Simões">Simoes</normalizedToken>
and Quartau 2013
</bibRefCitation>
). In some areas, they can be observed in large numbers singing together in a chorus (
<bibRefCitation author="Gogala, Matija" journalOrPublisher="Kataloge des Oberoesterreichischen Landesmuseums, Neue Folge, Denisia, 4" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5742831" refString="Gogala, Matija, 2002. Zikaden: Leafhoppers, Planthoppers and Cicadas (Insecta: Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha). Kataloge des Oberoesterreichischen Landesmuseums, Neue Folge, Denisia, 4" title="Zikaden: Leafhoppers, Planthoppers and Cicadas (Insecta: Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha)" year="2002">Gogala 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
